Package soot.jimple.infoflow.problems.rules.backward

Class BackwardsSourcePropagationRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • soot.jimple.infoflow.problems.rules.AbstractTaintPropagationRule
      • soot.jimple.infoflow.problems.rules.backward.BackwardsSourcePropagationRule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITaintPropagationRule, IAdditionalFlowSinkPropagationRule
    public class BackwardsSourcePropagationRule
extends AbstractTaintPropagationRule
implements IAdditionalFlowSinkPropagationRule
    Rule for recording abstractions that arrive at sources The sources are swapped for the sinks, thats why all the other methods call for sink even though they work on the sources
    Author:
    Steven Arzt, Tim Lange
